newsitem.title: USA: CSCE world sugar ends up, March breaks resistance.
newsitem.headline: CSCE world sugar ends up, March breaks resistance.

text.p: CSCE world sugar futures settled near the highs, with the most-active March contract overcoming nearby resistance at 10.40 cents per lb.
Dealers attributed gains to light trade buying and commission house short covering, which accelerated in the afternoon and lifted the market over its near-term hurdle.
Traders Thursday will look for the contract to pierce firm resistance pegged at 10.50 cents in March, they said.
Volume was thin, estimated at a mere 8,972 lots.
March ended 0.07 higher at 10.42 cents, traded 10.43 to 10.34. May gained 0.03 to 10.54, while the back months finished 0.03 to 0.01 firmer.

Firm support was placed at 10.21, where a double bottom has formed on the charts Dec 3 and April 30. Sell stops are likely to be triggered below that level, pressuring March to key psychological 10.00 cents, analysts said.
